				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Variations on a Theme: Supplementary Rules for Monopoly" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>A collection of Monopoly variants, intended (except for the last) to be used separately:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The Investment Fund allows players to invest their money. The principal can never be taken out but every time a player passes GO they receive 10% interest. This can radically change the nature of the game, among other things speeding it up significantly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The Auction Game requires all properties to be auctioned when landed on for the first time. This tends to slow the game down and reduces reliance on luck somewhat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Building Past Hotels allows further property development. This makes the cheaper monopolies more interesting. A set of extended property cards is provided which show the additional costs and rents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Ruffles and Flourishes, a set of small tweaks which can be used together or separately. One is a new set of &amp;quot;wahoo&amp;quot; cards which can all be kept until a player wants to use them; a set is provided.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
